President Obama announced several key administration posts on March 19, 2009. Jon Wellinghoff was designated as Chairman of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (FERC), while Suedeen Kelly was nominated for re-appointment as a Commissioner at FERC. Other nominations included Elizabeth King for Assistant Secretary for Legislative Affairs at the Department of Defense, T. Michael Kerr for Assistant Secretary for Administration and Management at the Department of Labor, Gabriella Gomez for Assistant Secretary for Legislation and Congressional Affairs at the Department of Education, Dr. Joe Leonard, Jr. for Assistant Secretary for Civil Rights at the United States Department of Agriculture, Cameron F. Kerry for General Counsel at the Department of Commerce, Robert S. Rivkin for General Counsel at the Department of Transportation, and M. Patricia Smith for Solicitor at the Department of Labor. President Obama expressed confidence in these individuals and their commitment to public service.